Tags.string 'NodeComment': On Interact "on" of one of the components in the array, we increase the count of active triggers. If they are more than the triggers needed (which can also be set by the level designer) we call open door

The door has an array of triggers, meaning designers can require multiple pressure plate interactions before the door opens.You can implement different door logic via the events triggered by the interaction component.
Triggers are in an exposed array that can be edited per instance. If the level designer added references to triggers (buttons or pressure plates) we assign OnInteract event for all of them.
On Interact "off" of one of the components in the array, we decrease the amount of active triggers and close the door
Open and close door playing a timeline forward or reverse. The numbers for the Y location of the doors were determined through testing and iteration.
